
1.Login to the VM and Add the user:

# useradd <username>

# cd /home

2.Login as a user

#sudo su - <username> or su - username

3.If there is no .ssh need to create manually and give the permission

#mkdir.ssh

#chmod 700 .ssh

#cd /.ssh

#ls

#vim authorized_keys

Paste  the user ssh-rsa key here and provide this permission

 {chmod 600 authorized_keys}

Exit from the user login as a root user, then follow below steps.

vim /etc/sudoers

## Same thing without a password

# %wheel    ALL=(ALL)   NOPASSWD: ALL

username  ALL=(ALL)   NOPASSWD: ALL
